    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add>Yiddish</add></p>
			<p><placeName>N<hi rend="underline">o</hi> 9 Reade St N. Y</placeName>&#58;</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p><placeName>Walnut Street</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p><hi rend="underline">Paide</hi></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><add><hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi></add></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> Tuesday&#44; 5th of</p> 
          <p rend="align(right)"><date>Nisan &#40;April&#41; 1851</date>.</p>
			<p>May the God of the Universe grant life&#44; etc&#44;<lb/> <addressee>Rabbi Yitzchek Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">With an expression of greetings I come<lb/> to beg of you for an unusual favor.<lb/> A year ago&#44; you&#8212;<add>&#63;</add> printed Shema Yisreels&#42;<lb/> written by <persName>Mr. Bernahl</persName>&#44; and <persName>Mr. A. Hart</persName><lb/> answered that the die has been destroyed and<lb/> no more are to be had&#44; and <del>you</del> I came to<lb/> the conclusion that <del>you</del> I ought to make a<lb/> new die&#44; which <del>you</del> I did&#44; making many<lb/> changes and improvements in it&#44; so<lb/> that it might agree with the Divine<lb/> command. But before doing this I asked the<lb/> lawyer <persName>Joachinson</persName> whether it is allowed.<lb/> His answer was&#44; &#34;Certainly&#44; since you made<lb/> and want to make many improvements.&#34;<lb/> I then extended &#36;155.&#44; not a cent of mine&#44;<lb/> but money of my friends who assisted me.</p>
			<p>&#42;a group of Biblical quotations&#44; usually attached to the<lb/> walls over the bed of a woman who had just given birth.</p>
			<p rend="align(center)"><date>4&#45;5&#45;1851</date></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p>Now I am told that before selling I<lb/> must inquire more carefully about the<lb/> laws and customs of this land&#44; since every<lb/> thing of this sort is prohibited. That is<lb/> why I hope that you my friend will<lb/> do me this favor to write to <persName>Mr. Bernahl</persName><lb/> for permission to reprint the Shima Yisrael<lb/> and sell them. My view is that you should<lb/> not reveal that they are already printed<lb/> &#34;but the wise men has eyes in his head&#34;<lb/> and you may as you please. I do this<lb/> only to save my life&#44; to be able to<lb/> return the borrowed money&#44; and not to<lb/> make enemies for myself. But God<lb/> who knows the hidden things knows that<lb/> the fault lies with <persName>Joachinson</persName>. I have<lb/> no doubt you will do this kindness<lb/> and help me as much as possible&#44; in order to save my life. God will reward<lb/> you doubly&#44; etc. etc. Writing with weak<lb/> hands and shaking knees&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Simeon Cohen Nost</persName>&#44; <placeName>9 Reade St. N. Y.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><date>4&#45;5&#45;1851</date></p>
          
        </body>
